The paper discusses the development of a metatheory for ontologies, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of category theory, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL). The paper also mentions the modular design of object-level ontologies, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
